{"word":"ὀμνύω","slug":"ὀμνύω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>ὀμνύω</el></b> [related form in <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ Skt.\">Skt.</a>] ‘take an oath affirming veracity of what one says’, <b>swear <a href='B:470 5:34'>Mt 5:34</a>; <a href='B:480 6:23'>Mk 6:23</a>; <a href='B:480 14:71'>14:71</a></b> (not mere profanity); <b><a href='B:510 2:30'>Ac 2:30</a>; <a href='B:650 3:11'>Hb 3:11</a>;</b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ w.\">w.</a> cognate <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ acc.\">acc.</a> <el>ὅρϰον</el> <b><a href='B:490 1:73'>Lk 1:73</a>.</b> Warrant for the truth one affirms is expressed <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ w.\">w.</a> the <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ acc.\">acc.</a> <b><a href='B:660 5:12'>Js 5:12</a></b> and in various prepositional phrases: <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ w.\">w.</a> <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἐν\">ἐν</a></el> <b><a href='B:470 5:36'>Mt 5:36</a></b> and <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ oft.\">oft.</a> in Mt; <b><a href='B:730 10:6'>Rv 10:6</a>;</b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ w.\">w.</a> <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:κατά\">κατά</a></el> <b><a href='B:650 6:13'>Hb 6:13</a>, <a href='B:650 6:16'>16</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:ὄμνυμι\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:ὁμοθυμαδόν\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}